    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Fellowship.<br />
I bed up to 4 (risky, but mostly I bed 3) to get site 1(Hollin). I start with Aragon, and play more companions only from site 3 onwards. Elendil&#8217;s valor&#8217;s and Swordarm&#8217;s will keep you save until then) But with only two companions there isn&#8217;t enough twilight for shadow players.<br />
I&#8217;ve put in 2 hobbit swords and stealth&#8217;s to give Frodo some protection on the first few sites.<br />
Hollin helps you against people who rely on Prancing Pony to get Aragon and gives you more twilight if your opponent plays companions at site one.<br />
I don&#8217;t have any Sword of Condor&#8217;s(trying to get one) so I only play Boromir because he is n man character, most of my Fellowship event&#8217;s is for them.<br />
Sam is there for cannon fodder, but I try to keep him alive for site 7,8 or 9.<br />
Legolas and Gandalf (with sleep Caradhras)is there to boost the fellowship and as you move on.<br />
I put in a &#8220;A wizards never late&#8221; to get Gandalf more quickly because I have his sword.<br />
Being only a 60 card deck  I usually  get my companions out from site four, or at least one.<br />
<br />
Shadow:<br />
I play a Standard Uruk deck, but I would like some help and suggestions on new  themes involving Uruks.<br />
I don&#8217;t have any &#8220;Troop of Uruk &#8220; cards, and only one captain and leutenant.<br />
I do have a sword for Lurtz, but I don&#8217;t play it&#8230; never get them out together.<br />
